RACE.FOOTNOTES: GET'EM TIGER was forwardly placed away from the start, stalked the decent early pace into the turn, advanced to press the pace to the quarter marker, drew to even terms with MAYCEE JO inside of the furlong pole, battled with that rival to deep stretch, took a narrow lead in the final yards and held well at the finish to determinedly prevail. MAYCEE JO broke alertly, showed speed in the early stages and set the pace to the turn, was pressed along the bend by GET'EM TIGER, held a narrow advantage on that rival into the stretch, met the bid of GET'EM TIGER inside of the furlong pole, gamely battled to deep stretch and just missed at the wire, while well clear of the rest for second. MISS SKI tracked the early pace from the inside, chased the leading pair along the turn, was not able to make headway on the leaders in the stretch and held for third at the finish. BIG GIFT was a bit slow into stride early on and settled off of the early pace, was roused three wide heading to the quarter marker, was floated out at mid-stretch when BLUSHING BAY lost action, made a mild rally in deep stretch and just missed for third. GOING TO SHABOOMS settled off of the early pace, chased two wide to the quarter marker and did not factor. BLUSHING BAY was crowded a bit at the start and was off a step slowly, tracked the early pace while outside of rivals, lost ground on the turn while two wide, lost action into the stretch, was pulled up at the furlong marker and walked off under her own power.

DUST MAKER settled inside of rivals leaving the break, was a bit hard to place entering the first turn and was shuffled back at the seven-eighths marker, was steered to the two path into the backstretch run and was unhurried to the half-mile pole, came three wide to the quarter marker, improved position into the stretch and closed willingly in the final stages. MISTY CAT tracked the early pace while outside of rivals and came three wide into the backstretch run, was well positioned while two wide into the far turn, needed more in the stretch run and finished evenly in the final stages. AIRKITA was forwardly placed into the first turn and tracked the early pace from the inside, saved all of the ground to the second turn, chased the top two into the stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. LYINATTHEBAR was a bit hard to place in the early running and drifted out entering the first turn, settled in the two path into the backstretch run, lost position at the half-mile marker and did not factor. BLOSSOMING settled outside of runners leaving the break, checked in tight quarters entering the first turn and tracked the pace four wide into the backstretch run, improved position heading to the half-mile marker and was well placed into the far turn, raced within aim while three then four wide nearing the top of the stretch, could not keep pace into the drive and gave way.

DAWN AT LAST was sent leaving an alert beginning and dictated terms in the early running, set a fast pace into the turn and carved quick fractions to the quarter marker, was confronted by BOLD MISTRESS at the furlong marker, battled inside of that rival to the sixteenth-pole, lost the lead into deep stretch, gamely came again in the final yards and just missed for the win at the finish, while holding for the place. JAYS ANGEL was forwardly placed in the early running and tracked the quick pace while outside of rivals, chased three wide along the turn and lost ground into the stretch, re-rallied inside of the furlong marker, finished well in deep stretch and missed for the win and place, while holding safely for the show. BACALAR bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, chased the solid early pace from the inside, tipped two wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in the final stages and was outkicked. LION'S LAIR lacked early speed and settled along the inside into the turn, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch and offered mild late rally while on the left lead. ZAKKIYYAH tracked the solid pace while outside of rivals, chased three wide to the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and lacked a late response.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: A CROWN FOR KITTEN unhurried from the break and allowed to settle on the rail, got a dream trip down the backstretch, moved into contention in hand through the far turn, tipped out to the two path for the stretch run, responded when roused at the top of the stretch and proved too much for the rest despite wandering a bit in mid-stretch. CALLHERCONTESSA broke in at the start, bothering UNFAITHFUL WAYS, a few strides later overcorrected into the path of WARRIOR'S MOON, then had to steady when PRINCESA DEL TIGRE took the path at the junction to the main course, tracked the pace three deep to the far turn, started to rally from the three furlong pole, fanned four wide into the stretch and rallied for the second spot. UNFAITHFUL WAYS had to check briefly just after the start then was content to trail well behind the field through the early stages, began to move closer down the backstretch, then rallied in earnest with three furlongs to go, kept to the inside through the turn, had to idle in traffic mid-stretch, found room along the rail and ran on well to grab third. PROOF OF JAZZ broke well, gained the lead through the first turn and proceeded uncontested until the far turn, responded when challenged with a quarter mile to run, had a little trouble changing leads at the top of the stretch and was outfinished in the final furlong. PRINCESA DEL TIGRE broke out at the start then went to challenge for the lead , angled over sharply near the end of the chute causing CALLHERCONTESSA to have to take up, was dueling for the lead going into the clubhouse turn then ceded the pacesetting duties to PROOF OF JAZZ, stalked that one two deep down the backstretch under some restraint, bid approaching the quarter-mile marker but could not produce the needed response. WARRIOR'S MOON showed little speed from the break, raced well behind the pace to the far turn, came under a ride from the three-furlong marker, was able to keep pace with the pack down the stretch but unable to improve position.

R SWEET CANDY was allowed to settle leaving the break, drifted out entering the first turn and floated out MS LIMONCELLO leaving the seven furlong marker, tracked the pace two wide into the backstretch run, was guided outside of rivals along the far turn and improved position while four wide at the quarter marker, continued that four wide bid into the stretch, vied for the lead inside of the furlong marker, could not match strides with VALENCE in deep stretch and was outfinished, while holding safely at the end for second. ACCLAIMED PREACHER took back off of the early pace and tracked from the second flight into the first turn, tracked three wide into the backstretch run, was well placed heading to the quarter marker, loomed three wide nearing the quarter pole, vied for the lead in upper stretch then took command approaching the furlong marker, was overtaken in in the final sixteenth, weakened in deep stretch and was just edged for third in the final strides. UNION HEIRESS settled off of the early pace and saved ground into the first turn, tracked from the inside through the backstretch run, gained ground along the far turn, waited for racing room while two wide nearing the quarter marker, found room into upper stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in the final stages and passed tiring rivals in deep stretch. VHAGAR was squeezed at the start, clipped heels and spotted the field several lengths in the early going, settled along the rail into the first turn, trailed through the backstretch run, improved position while five wide along the far turn, continued that bid into the stretch, could not sustain her rally into the final furlong and flattened out. MIRAGE CODE was asked for early speed, assumed command and sped to the lead into the first turn, set decent fractions through the backstretch run, was confronted nearing the quarter marker, stopped in upper stretch, was eased through the lane and walked off under his own power.

MAJESTIC OOPS was up on the pace through the first furlong then dropped off the pace before the turn, came under a ride from the three furlong marker, turned for home with only one beaten, swung out in mid-stretch for clear run and surged in the late stages to gain the place. CRYSTAL PROOF bobbled at the break, but was quickly into stride and up on the pace early, inherited the the lead near the five-sixteenth marker when MORNING ADDICITION stopped running, battled TURA LURA to deep stretch, weakened inside the sixteenth pole and was outfinished.
